    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single, long-scroll page with a sticky top navigation bar. The nav links act as anchor links, smoothly scrolling the user to the corresponding section. An IntersectionObserver is used for scroll-spying, highlighting the active link in the navigation as the user scrolls. This structure provides a fluid, report-style layout, allowing users to consume the content linearly while still providing quick navigation. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Strategic Context: Presented with clear typography and highlighted key stats to establish CXT's market position. Goal: Inform. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Pain-Point Playbook: Uses interactive cards with Heroicons for four main themes and a dynamic, filterable HTML table for the 'Rosetta Stone' matrix. Goal: Compare & Organize. Interaction: Dropdown filters update the table content. Method: Vanilla JS for table filtering. Justification: Makes the complex data set of logistics challenges explorable and easy to digest.
        - Prospecting Engine: A tabbed interface separates the three main targeting strategies (Technographic, Signal-Based, Lookalike). Goal: Organize. Interaction: Clicking tabs reveals relevant content. Method: HTML/Tailwind/JS. Justification: A standard, intuitive UI pattern for grouping distinct but related strategies.
        - Growth Levers: Uses a responsive grid of cards to present Video, Webinar, and Events tactics. A custom HTML/CSS funnel diagram illustrates the video strategy. Goal: Inform. Method: HTML/Tailwind. Justification: Visually separates and highlights the key proposed tactics.
        - GTM Frameworks: A custom HTML/CSS diagram visualizes the Bowtie model. An interactive accordion explains the SPICED framework with detailed sample questions. Goal: Organize & Inform. Interaction: Clicking accordion headers reveals details. Method: HTML/Tailwind/JS. Justification: Visual and interactive elements make these abstract frameworks easier to understand.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
